## Search

```bash
eval "$(~/.claude/skills/ohmystack/bin/ohmystack-slug 2>/dev/null)"
~/.claude/skills/ohmystack/bin/ohmystack-learnings-search --query "USER_QUERY" --limit 20 2>/dev/null || echo "No matches."
```

Replace USER_QUERY with the user's search terms. Present results clearly.

When the query is broad, ambiguous, or asks for "best"/"recommended" approaches, dispatch parallel research before answering:

```typescript
task(subagent_type="explore", run_in_background=true, load_skills=[], prompt="[CONTEXT]: /learn search for [USER_QUERY]. [GOAL]: Find relevant internal learnings and adjacent project context. [REQUEST]: Search learnings entries, referenced files, and nearby project history for matches, variants, and contradictory evidence.")
task(subagent_type="librarian", run_in_background=true, load_skills=[], prompt="[CONTEXT]: /learn search for [USER_QUERY]. [GOAL]: Find external best practices related to the discovered patterns. [REQUEST]: Look up authoritative guidance, common industry patterns, and compare them with the internal learnings you were given.")
```

Present internal learnings first, then clearly separate any external best-practice context from Librarian.

